I look forward to the October coloring challenge and the months thereafter.😁😁😁Thank you @happydartist 😁👍

Entry for the August 2018 Coloring Challenge.
This is a competition created by @happydartist, an artist that creates amazing artworks.
Essentially the competition requires the participant to color-in one sketch created by @happydartist 
I have started a bit late, but have to submit, since today is the last day so there are some areas which can still be improved, but will start early for next month’s challenge. What do you think? 😁☘️😄🌿😃🍀

「好」How 😄😁😆👨🏻‍🎨🎨🎊👌 Basically, the Chinese character in the middle is 好， which also sounds like “How”, and 好 means “Good!”. However the interesting part is that the Chinese character 好 is actually made up of another two Chinese characters 女 and 子 which means female and male. So there is a subliminal meaning! Essentially  the meaning “How” means “how are we created?” “How is it decided that we are Male or Female.” We may be curious but it doesn’t really matter -  One is not superior over the other, so if we don’t look at each other’s weakness and rather focus on the strengths... the character 好 which means “Good” Is formed.

Song of a million Birds🦅🐥🐧🐦🐤🐣 Birds flying around freely because they have found the purpose of life. The shape of the paint strokes looks like [人], which means human in Chinese. It may be perceived as the scene of humans finding their freedom (“purpose of life”) and singing with joy. 
Alternative Interpretations: -  Subliminal -  million birds can be translated into: [百萬鳥] in Chinese, and if one pronounces the characters (bǎi wàn niǎo), it sounds like “Buy One Now”
